This paper deals with the detection and analysis of paedophile activity in a P2P system, which involves aspects of computer security (cs.CR), information retrieval (cs.IR), and social networks (cs.SOC). The paper also discusses the design and evaluation of a detection tool, which could fall under the category of cybercrime (cs.CY). Overall, the paper covers a range of topics that could fit into multiple sub-categories, but the ones listed above are the most likely based on the content of the paper.
